title: For Sale:  Primary Weapons Systems MK116 Mod 1-P Rifle 16.1" Barrel .223 Wylde MFG # M116RA1B
postcontent: CHECK TO SEE IF FIREARM IS IN STOCK BEFORE PURCHASING ONLINE>Primary Weapons Systems MK116 Mod 1-P Rifle 16.1" Barrel .223 Wylde MFG # M116RA1B  Primary Weapons Systems MK116 Mod 1-P Rifle 16.1" Barrel .223 Wylde MFG # M116RA1B  The shortest of the non-NFA models with a removable muzzle device, the PWS Mod1-P MK116 Rifle is a crowd favorite. The MK116 is designed for a multitude of uses and retains lethal capability out to 500 meters with varying types of ammunition. The PWS Long Stroke Piston  The PWS long-stroke piston system combines the agility of the AR-15 with the reliability of the AK-47 into a sleek and efficient design.  Adjustable Gas Block  PWS three position adjustable gas block restricts gasses rather than venting them from the side. This allows the unused gas to exit from the front of the gun resulting in a quieter operation.  Position 1 is normal operation with standard and some military ammunition. Position 2 is for suppressed use with hotter loads such as a military ammunition. Position 3 is for suppressed use when running standard ammunition.    Smooth Recoil Impulse  A detachable floating piston head is attached to the operating rod which is securely attached to the carrier. With only one moving assembly, the PWS long-stroke piston system offers a lighter recoil impulse while at the same time providing increased longevity and durability.  FNC Life HD Barrels  Utilizing only the highest quality 416R stainless steel barrel blanks, MK1 barrels are turned in house then lithium embedded salt nitro-carburized treated (FNC Life HD) for hardness and corrosion resistance.  Twist & Chamber  Button rifled barrels feature a 1:8 twist, which accommodates 55 grain through 75 grain bullets with a high degree of accuracy. Chambered in .223 Wylde, MK1 barrels accept both 5.56 Nato and .223 Remington without sacrificing accuracy.  Profile  PWS engineers designed a barrel profile that reduces weight without decreasing accuracy.  Bolt Carrier Group  PWS bolt carrier groups are machined from tool steel at strict tolerances, then FNC Life HD coated for durability and to reduce fricition.  Mass  PWS engineers increased carrier mass to extend dwell time and delay unlock. As a resut the PWS bolt carrier group allows chamber pressure to be greatly reduced for easier extraction.  Minimized Contact Points  Gaps and channels between skid pads allow for fewer points of contact. This results in less fricition and keeps debrise from interfering with function.  Bolt  The PWS bolt system is optimized for the .223 wylde chamber and features a spring assist for ease of assembly.  Free-Floating Handguards  PWS engineers designed a handguard which is ergonomic as well as durable. Featuring the KeyMod interface, the Mod1-P series handguard eliminates unnecessary weight and allows for a wide range of accessory placement.  Picatinny Top Rail  Extruded and then machined from aircraft grade 6061 aluminum, every handguard comes standard with a full-length Picatinny top rail.  QD Attachments  Integral sling swivel attachment points round out the front and back of the handguard.  KeyMod  The KeyMod Interface System was developed for multiple accessory combatibility without the need for Picatinny rails surrounding your handguard. This improved design enhanced the rail's comfort and functionality without sacrificing strength and durability.  Upper & Lower Forgings  Understanding the importance of an ultra-reliable package that is as light as possible, mil-spec 7075 aluminum forging s are used for the upper and lower receivers. Each upper and lower are meticulously CNC-machined for perfect fit and function.  Coating  After machining and blasting, all aluminum parts are Hardcoat Annodized at Type III Mil-Spec, for corrosion and wear resistance.  Bravo Company Furniture  All PWS rifles ship with durable Bravo Company furniture.  Buffer  PWS engineers were able to pack a plethora of features into the PWS buffer tube.  Ratchet Locking Castle Nut & End Plate  The unique ratchet lock design requries no staking and integrates a QD sling mount into the end plate.  Carrier Tilt  Features a lip that extends into the receiver to support the back of the carrier to compensate for carrier tilt.  QD Attachments  Unlike aftermarket items, PWS EBT QD attachments are machined directly into the 4140 steel for durability and weight savings.  Debris  This impact extruded 7075 aluminum mil spec buffer tube features a fluted tube and enlarged drain holes for debris cleaning.  H2 Steel Body Buffer  Low contact points on the fluted shaft allow debris to fall into channels, while the low friction FNC Life HD coating keeps carbon from sticking to the 4140 steel body. The staked cross pin allows for durability under suppressed use.  Specifications  Weight: 6 lbs 13 oz Overall Length: 33" Barrel Length: 16.1" Muzzle Device: FSC 556
